FOODBORNE ILLNESS - INDIA (05): (JAMMU AND KASHMIR) RICE DISH
*************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Sat 2 Apr 2022
Source: Rising Kashmir [edited]
https://www.risingkashmir.com/-49-hospitalised-due-to-suspected-food-poisoning-in-Budgam-village-103744


At least 49 persons, many of them children, were hospitalized on Friday [1 Apr 2022] after consuming "Tehri" at Zagipora village of Chrari-Sharif of Central Kashmir's Budgam district. According to the reports, panic gripped Zaigipora village in Budgam after 49 people, many among them children, complained of stomachache. They are believed to have consumed "Tehri" and were shifted to different hospitals. Of them, 27 children were admitted at GB Pant hospital and 2 adults at SMHS hospital.

Medical Superintendent, GB Pant hospital, Dr Nazir Ahmad Chowdhary told Rising Kashmir that 27 children have been admitted in the hospital so far. "They consumed Tehri yesterday at around 5 pm. Today, they have been admitted to the hospital. They started vomiting and complained of diarrhoea, but now they are stable," he said.

Medical Superintendent, SMHS hospital, Dr Kanwaljeet Singh told Rising Kashmir that there are 2 adult patients admitted in the hospital. "Both are food poisoning cases. They have gastrointestinal infection," he said.

Dr Tajamul Hussain Khan, CMO Budgam, said that they have so far received about 20 people from the village at Sub District hospital Chararisharief. Other patients have been shifted to SMHS and GB Pant hospital for treatment.

[Byline: Rabiya Bashir]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED

[The etiology (or etiologies) of this foodborne illness is not clear.

"Tehri (also tahri, tehari or tayari) is a yellow rice dish in Awadhi cuisine. Spices are added to plain cooked rice for flavor and color. In one version of tehri, potatoes are added to the rice. In other variants soyabean chunks, vegetables, onions, tomatoes and many different spices are also added" (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tahri_(dish)).

Budgam district is a district in the Indian-administered union territory of Jammu and Kashmir. - Mod.LL

